    service4: "Disputes in the field of banking law",
    service5: "Bank loans, consumer loans, mortgages, collateral, sureties – all these are extremely popular and often necessary things in the modern life of a citizen, as well as business. On this basis, disputes arise between the banking institution and the borrower, especially in the case of existing loan debt. Disputes with banks are considered one of the most difficult categories of cases, since they entail not only material losses, but can also lead to eviction and, as a result, loss of housing. Therefore, a loan lawyer is extremely necessary when resolving a situation where a bank has filed a lawsuit and is foreclosing on property. <br><br> The banking sector covers an incredibly large number of different categories, but most often for advice to a credit lawyer they turn to the following issues: <br><br> - delay in repayment of debt <br> - eviction from mortgage property <br> - illegal accrual of interest and fines by the bank <br> - underestimation of the value of mortgage property when selling at auction <br> - microloan debt, threats of collectors <br><br> Turning to a lawyer for credit disputes you can get a qualified advice, and in the future, assistance in solving a problem with a banking institution or any other-which lender. <br> <br> How can a banking lawyer help you? <br> <br> - negotiate with the bank on repayment of credit debt at a discount <br> - represent your interests in courts and state bodies, participate in court sessions <br> - develop a debt repayment agreement (write - off, restructuring) and accompany you when signing it in a banking institution <br> - initiate the process of reducing the amount of accrued penalties <br> - reduce or completely write off the credit debt <br> - appeal against the actions of a public or private contractor, close enforcement proceedings, etc. <br><br> In this way, bank dispute attorneys at OTS law firm will help you reduce the amount of your debt, save your mortgage or mortgaged property, and avoid even bigger problems with the financial institution. We work all over Ukraine with all banks and financial companies, and most importantly – we have extensive experience in positive dispute resolution in favor of the client. The earlier you contact a lawyer, the more likely you are to protect your rights and legitimate interests. <br><br> <b>You can get legal advice and assistance from a lawyer by calling: +380 (67) 878-70-30</b>",

    service7: "Criminal lawyer",
